commitResults.messageBody:
If date and datePlayed occur within the same minute, but different millisecond, date.equals(datePlayed) will return false, but
datePlayed.equals(date) will return false. We need equals method to be transitive.

commitResults.messageBody:
Current constructors assume that minute field is to be considered. This will cause issues if the user adds dates without minute field.

New constructor created, and toString method will treat DatePlayed objects with minute fields differently from those without minute fields.

commitResults.messageBody:
GameEntry objects are considered to share the same identity if they are of the same gameType and share the same date and time.
GameEntry objects without their time indicated never have the same identity as any other GameEntry besides itself.

commitResults.messageBody:
GameEntryBuilder is used as a testing utility class to create GameEntry objects.

There should not be exceptions when using this class because it is invoked by the programmer to create test case objects.

Let's handle exceptions internally to remove the need to catch when using it to build test classes and cases.

CommandWindow is created to show a pop up window for user confirmation.
ClearCommandParser is used to determine the type of ClearCommand to be created.

A clear command from the user should not contain additional arguments, while
a clear command initiated by the app after user's confirmation should contain
an extra identifiable argument.
